Jacques Perron has been appointed president and CEO of dual-listed Pretium Resources (Pretivm), the owner of the Brucejack mine, north of Stewart, British Columbia. Perron was president, CEO and director of Thompson Creek Metals, which was bought by Centerra Gold in 2016. Among his previous senior executive positions in mining, he was president and CEO of St. Andrew Goldfields, senior VP of Iamgold and senior VP of Canada of Cambior. Perron succeeds Joseph Ovsenek, who was Pretivmâ€™s president and CEO since 2017, president since 2015 and executive VP and chief development officer from 2011 to 2015.